article.headline: Garry scores 20, South Dakota State takes down Duquesne 71-60 at Cayman Islands Classic
article.description: — Kalen Garry scored 20 points as South Dakota State beat Duquesne 71-60 on Sunday at the Cayman Islands Classic.
article.linkText: Garry scores 20, South Dakota State takes down Duquesne 71-60 at Cayman Islands Classic
article.story: GEORGE TOWN, George Town -- — Kalen Garry scored 20 points as South Dakota State beat Duquesne 71-60 on Sunday at the Cayman Islands Classic. Garry also had five rebounds for the Jackrabbits (5-1). Oscar Cluff scored 17 points while shooting 6 of 10 from the field and 5 for 6 from the free-throw line and added 11 rebounds and five assists. Matthew Mors had 15 points and shot 4 of 7 from the field, including 1 for 3 from 3-point range, and went 6 for 8 from the foul line. The Dukes (0-5) were led by Tre Dinkins, who recorded 19 points and two steals. Maximus Edwards added 11 points for Duquesne. Jake DiMichele finished with 10 points. South Dakota State was tied with Duquesne at the half, 33-33, with Garry (12 points) its high scorer before the break. Joe Sayler's 3-pointer with 8:54 remaining in the second half gave South Dakota State the lead for good at 52-51. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
